Busia sex workers on Sunday marked International Day to End Violence Against Sex Workers. They appealed to the national government to legalise prostitution. Busia Survivors programme officer Caroline Kemunto led the team to clean Busia police station compound after a peaceful demonstration. “We are subjected to constant harassment and arbitrary arrests before being charged in court,” she said. Kemunto added that some of their problems include men clients who refuse to use protection. Kemunto said men who refuse to use condoms are violent. Some of the male sex workers said they are proud of their work and should not be seen as outcasts. T here are 3,000 female sex workers and 500 men who have sex with men in Busia county. One male sex worker said, “I have clients in Kenya and Uganda.”